  keywords      = {rank4, read},
  review        = {In this paper, the authors propose an algorithm for efficient transportation in post-emergency situations. According to the authors, transportation of reliefs in a post-disaster scenario is of great importance, thus, an efficient as quick transportation route plan is needed in such situations. They combine two vehicle routing problem (VRP) models: cumulative VRP (cum-VRP) and Multi-depot VRP (MDVP), creating a new solution called cum-MDVRP. They then developed a novel hybrid ant colony optimization based algorithm (ACO) called ACOMR to solve the cum-MDVRP problem, generating a set of feasible solutions to the problem, returning efficient routes for relief transportation. To evaluate their proposal, the authors simulated their algorithm against two recent published solutions: two-phase heirustic algorithm (TPH) and the parallel improved ant colony optimization algorithm (PIACO). The simulations have shown that ACOMR returned more stable and better solutions compared to the other algorithms. Also, ACOMR showed to have a good response time.

